    • Constructor Detail

      • FhirEncoders

        public FhirEncoders​(FhirContext context,
                    au.csiro.pathling.encoders.datatypes.DataTypeMappings mappings,
                    int maxNestingLevel,
                    Set<String> openTypes,
                    boolean enableExtensions)
        Consumers should generally use the forR4() method, but this is made available for test purposes and additional experimental mappings.
        Parameters:
        context - the FHIR context to use.
        mappings - mappings between Spark and FHIR data types.
        maxNestingLevel - maximum nesting level for expansion of recursive data types.
        openTypes - the list of types that are encoded within open types, such as extensions.
        enableExtensions - true if FHIR extension should be enabled.
